From: "Ooi, Joyce" <joyce.ooi@intel.com>
Date: Fri, 2 Dec 2016 10:59:08 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 4560/4706] Revert "hid: intel-ish-hid: Add
 PCI_DEV_FLAGS_NO_D3 flag in ISH PCI device
 driver"

commit b2fc4addbc7c56cb886910e3943113fc1b8d1af4 from
git://git.yoctoproject.org/linux-yocto-4.1

This reverts commit 894e903b51e8 ("hid: intel-ish-hid: Add
PCI_DEV_FLAGS_NO_D3 flag in ISH PCI device driver").
The changes of this patch are already included in upstream ISH drivers.

Signed-off-by: Ooi, Joyce <joyce.ooi@intel.com>
---
 drivers/hid/intel-ish-hid/ipc/pci-ish.c |    2 --
 1 files changed, 0 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/hid/intel-ish-hid/ipc/pci-ish.c b/drivers/hid/intel-ish-hid/ipc/pci-ish.c
index 526c170..4447eda 100644
--- a/drivers/hid/intel-ish-hid/ipc/pci-ish.c
+++ b/drivers/hid/intel-ish-hid/ipc/pci-ish.c
@@ -147,8 +147,6 @@ static int ish_probe(struct pci_dev *pdev, const struct pci_device_id *ent)
 
 	dev->pdev = pdev;
 
-	pdev->dev_flags |= PCI_DEV_FLAGS_NO_D3;
-
 	/* request and enable interrupt */
 	ret = request_irq(pdev->irq, ish_irq_handler, IRQF_NO_SUSPEND,
 			  KBUILD_MODNAME, dev);
